Mechyrdia isn't a dictatorship, it's a liberal democracy, so I'm going to do this with another country in Mechyrdia lore instead: Fulkreykk!

Always an absolutist state where the leader has complete and total control over every aspect of the nation

Not true in the First Fulkreyksk Authoritariat, only somewhat true in the Second Fulkreyksk Authoritariat. In fact, during the First Authoritariat, the Thedish Assembly (the legislature of Fulkreykk) kicked Jorh Karnas out of his position as Forarr (the head of state of Fulkreykk) because he launched an invasion of the Drakhassi Federation that ended in disaster.

If not some generic 'evil empire', is thematically based on Nazi Germany, North Korea, or the Soviet Union

Thematically it's based on Adam Dressler's German Reich from that old Hoi4 mod, an alt-hist where Germany lost World War 1. But much of the aesthetic of paganism is stripped away and replaced with an aesthetic of high science - which fits Fulkreykk's ideology. Hence the valknut being colored in RGB.

Even if they're thematically based on a RL dictatorship, may or may not actually ideologically match or be similar to the RL dictatorship, but would often rather just be generically 'evil' and 'oppressive'

Fulkreykk isn't generically evil and oppressive, far from it. Their whole government is centered around the ideology of Witenskaftsregaeryng, or "science governance". Originally, the vision of Vrankenn Kassck (the founder of Fulkreykk) was that the government would be controlled by scientific knowledge. However, under the later rule of Praethoris Khorr, that would be inverted, so that Fulkreykk, for much of its existence, operates under the fact that scientific knowledge is controlled by government.

Will make threads/posts to show off how 'evil' they are and how much they oppress their citizens, but it always comes off as tryhard and edgy

Yeah no, I don't do this.

MILITARY IS SUPREME. Tons of factbooks and shit about their military (which is, of course, always the greatest military power imaginable) and little about anything else

I think I have exactly one factbook that could be called a military factbook about Fulkreykk, and its a gallery of 3d ship models.

Like your own lore has Gandoor going through a civil war and being under a dictatorship. There’s got to be some sort of scars that aren’t fixed yet.

That's kinda what I was getting at.

There's nothing wrong with "nice" or even "utopian" nations when there's at least some backstory as to how they got there. It's ludicrous to imagine that there's a utopia-style nation out there that has never struggled internally or externally, or has no interesting history to write about.
